obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10991)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10991&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Petroleum`
  line `and Natural Gas Regulatory Board Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
  line
  line `(4) It applies to refining, processing, storage, transportation, distribution, marketing and sale of`
  line `petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas excluding production of crude oil and natural gas.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st October, 2007 (except s. 16), vide notification No. G.S.R. 637(E) dated 1st October, 2007, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `15th July, 2010,--Section 16, vide notification No. G.S.R. 596(E), dated 12th July, 2010, see Gazetted of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10992)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10992&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "affiliate code of conduct" means the code of conduct governing entities engaged in storage,`
  line `transmission, distribution, marketing and sale of natural gas under sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(b) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal referred to in section 30;`
  line
  line `(c) "appointed day" means the date on which the Board is established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "authorised entity" means an entity--`
  line
  line `(A) registered by the Board under section 15--`
  line
  line `(i) to market any notified petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to establish and operate liquefied natural gas terminals, or`
  line
  line `(B) authorised by the Board under section 16--`
  line
  line `(i) to lay, build, operate or expand a common carrier or contract carrier, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to lay, build, operate or expand a city or local natural gas distribution network;`
  line
  line `(e) 'auto liquefied petroleum gas" means a mixture of certain light hydrocarbons derived from`
  line `petroleum, which are gaseous at normal ambient temperature and atmospheric pressure but may be`
  line `condensed to the liquid state at normal ambient temperature by the application of moderate pressure,`
  line `and which conform to such specifications for use as fuel in vehicles, as the Central Government may,`
  line `in consultation with the Bureau of Indian Standards, notify from time to time;`
  line
  line `(f) "Board" means the Petroleum and Natural Gas Regulatory Board established under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) 'Bureau of Indian Standards" means the Bureau of Indian Standards established under section`
  line `3 of the Bureau of Indian Standards Act, 1986 (63 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(h) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(i) "city or local natural gas distribution network" means an inter-connected network of gas`
  line `pipelines and the associated equipment used for transporting natural gas from a bulk supply high`
  line `pressure transmission main to the medium pressure distribution grid and subsequently to the service`
  line `pipes supplying natural gas to domestic, industrial or commercial premises and CNG stations situated`
  line `in a specified geographical area.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the expressions "high pressure" and "medium`
  line `pressure" shall mean such pressure as the Central Government may, by notification, specify to be`
  line `high pressure or, as the case may be, medium pressure;`
  line
  line `(j) "common carrier" means such pipelines for transportation of petroleum, petroleum products`
  line `and natural gas by more than one entity as the Board may declare or authorise from time to time on a`
  line `non-discriminatory open access basis under sub-section (3) of section 20, but does not include`
  line `pipelines laid to supply--`
  line
  line `(i) petroleum products or natural gas to a specific consumer; or`
  line
  line `(ii) crude oil;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, a contract carrier shall be treated as a common`
  line `carrier, if-`
  line
  line `(i) such contract carrier has surplus capacity over and above the firm contracts entered`
  line `into; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the firm contract period has expired.`
  line
  line `(k) "CNG station" means filling station where one or more dispensing units are provided for sale`
  line `of compressed natural gas;`
  line
  line `(l) "compressed natural gas or CNG" means natural gas used as fuel for vehicles, typically`
  line `compressed to the pressure ranging from 200 to 250 bars in the gaseous state;`
  line
  line `(m) "contract carrier" means such pipelines for transportation of petroleum, petroleum products`
  line `and natural gas by more than one entity pursuant to firm contracts for at least one year as may be`
  line `declared or authorised by the Board from time to time under sub-section (3) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(n) "dealer" means a person, association of persons, firm, company or co-operative society, by`
  line `whatsoever name called or referred to, and appointed by an oil company to purchase, receive, store`
  line `and sell motor spirit, high speed diesel, superior kerosene oil, auto liquefied petroleum gas or natural`
  line gas;
  line
  line `(o) 'distributor" means a person, association of persons, firm, company or co-operative society,`
  line `by whatsoever name called or referred to, and appointed by an oil company to purchase, receive, store`
  line `and sell to consumers liquefied petroleum gas in cylinders;`
  line
  line `(p) "entity" means a person, association of persons, firm, company or co-operative society, by`
  line `whatsoever name called or referred to, other than a dealer or distributor, and engaged or intending to`
  line `be engaged in refining, processing, storage, transportation, distribution, marketing, import and export`
  line `of petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas including laying of pipelines for transportation of petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas, or laying, building, operating or expanding city or`
  line `local natural gas distribution network or establishing and operating a liquefied natural gas terminal;`
  line
  line `(q) 'exchange of products shall" mean giving and receiving of a petroleum product in accordance`
  line `with an agreement entered into by the concerned entities;`
  line
  line `(r) "high speed diesel" means any hydrocarbon oil (excluding mineral colza oil and turpentine`
  line `substitute), which conforms to such specifications for use as fuel in compression ignition engines, as`
  line `the Central Government may, in consultation with the Bureau of Indian Standards, notify from time to`
  line time;
  line
  line `(s) "kerosene or superior kerosene oil" means a middle distillate mixture of hydrocarbons which`
  line `conforms to such specifications, as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Bureau of`
  line `Indian Standards, notify from time to time;`
  line
  line `(t) "liquefied natural gas terminal" means the facilities and infrastructure required to--`
  line
  line `(i) receive liquefied natural gas;`
  line
  line `(ii) store liquefied natural gas;`
  line
  line `(iii) enable regasification of liquefied natural gas; and`
  line
  line `(iv) transport regasified liquefied natural gas till the outside boundaries of the facility;`
  line
  line `(u) "liquefied petroleum gas" means a mixture of light hydrocarbons containing propane,`
  line `isobutene, normal butane, butylenes, or such other substance which is gaseous at normal ambient`
  line `temperature and atmospheric pressure but may be condensed to liquid state at normal ambient`
  line `temperature by the application of pressure and conforms to such specifications, as the Central`
  line `Government may, in consultation with the Bureau of Indian Standards, notify from time to time;`
  line
  line `(v) "local distribution entity" means an entity authorised by the Board under section 20 to lay,`
  line `build, operate or expand a city or local natural gas distribution network;`
  line
  line `(w) "marketing service obligations" means obligations--`
  line
  line `(i) to set up marketing infrastructure and retail outlets in remote areas in respect of notified`
  line `petroleum and petroleum products;`
  line
  line `(ii) to maintain minimum stock of notified petroleum and petroleum products;`
  line
  line `(iii) of a local distribution entity to supply natural gas to consumers; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such other obligations as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(x) "maximum retail price" means the maximum price fixed by an entity at which the petroleum,`
  line `petroleum products and natural gas may be sold to the retail consumers and includes all taxes, cess`
  line `and levies, local or otherwise and freight or commission payable to the dealers;`
  line
  line `(y) "member" means a member of the Board appointed under sub-section (1) of section 4 and`
  line `includes the Member (Legal) and the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(z) "motor spirit" means any hydrocarbon oil (excluding crude mineral oil) used as fuel in spark`
  line `ignition engines which conforms to such specifications, as the Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Bureau of Indian Standards, notify from time to time;`
  line
  line `(za) "natural gas" means gas obtained from bore-holes and consisting primarily of hydrocarbons`
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) gas in liquid state, namely, liquefied natural gas and regasified liquefied natural gas,`
  line
  line `(ii) compressed natural gas,`
  line
  line `(iii) gas imported through transnational pipelines, including CNG or liquefied natural gas,`
  line
  line `(iv) gas recovered from gas hydrates as natural gas,`
  line
  line `(v) methane obtained from coal seams, namely, coal bed methane,`
  line
  line `but does not include helium occurring in association with such hydrocarbons;`
  line
  line `(zb) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `notified with its cognate meanings and grammatical variations, shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(zc) "notified petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas" means such petroleum, petroleum`
  line `products and natural gas as the Central Government may notify from time to time, after being`
  line `satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do for maintaining or increasing their supplies or for`
  line `securing their equitable distribution or ensuring adequate availability;`
  line
  line `(zd) 'oil company" means a company registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and`
  line `includes an association of persons, society or firm, by whatsoever name called or referred to, for`
  line `carrying out an activity relating to petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas;`
  line
  line `(ze) "petroleum" means any liquid hydrocarbon or mixture of hydrocarbons, and any inflammable`
  line `mixture (liquid, viscous or solid) containing any liquid hydrocarbon, including crude oil and liquefied`
  line `petroleum gas, and the expression 'petroleum product' shall mean any product manufactured from`
  line petroleum;
  line
  line `(zf) "pipeline access code" means the code to establish a framework for third party access to`
  line `pipelines under sub-clause (i) of clause (e) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(zg) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zh) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zi) "restrictive trade practice" means a trade practice which has, or may have, the effect of`
  line `preventing, distorting or restricting competition in any manner and in particular,--`
  line
  line `(i) which tends to obstruct the flow of capital or resources into the stream of production, or`
  line
  line `(ii) which tends to bring about manipulation of prices, or conditions of delivery or to affect`
  line `the flow of supplies in the market relating to petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas or`
  line `services in such manner as to impose on the consumers unjustified costs or restrictions;`
  line
  line `(zj) "retail outlet" means filling station where one or more dispensing pumps have been provided`
  line `for sale of motor spirit, high speed diesel, auto-liquefied petroleum gas or natural gas and includes`
  line `distributorship for liquefied petroleum gas or dealership for superior kerosene oil or CNG stations;`
  line
  line `(zk) "retail" service obligations means obligations of dealers and distributors for maintaining`
  line `supplies to consumers throughout the specified working hours and of specified quality, quantity and`
  line `display of maximum retail price of notified petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas including`
  line `CNG and such other obligations, as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(zl) "rules" means rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zm) "Secretary" means the Secretary of the Board;`
  line
  line `(zn) "transportation rate", in relation to common carrier or contract carrier or a city or local`
  line `natural gas distribution network, means such rate for moving each unit of petroleum, petroleum`
  line `products or natural gas as may be fixed by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10993)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10993&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established, for the purposes of this Act, a Board`
  line `to be called the Petroleum and Natural Gas Regulatory Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of a Chairperson, a Member (Legal) and three other members to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The head office of the Board shall be at New Delhi and regional offices at such places as the`
  line `Board may deem necessary having regard to public interest and magnitude of the work.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10994)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and other members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10994&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall appoint the Chairperson and other members of the Board from amongst persons of`
  line `eminence in the fields of petroleum and natural gas industry, management, finance, law, administration or`
  line `consumer affairs:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be appointed as Member (Legal) unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is qualified to be a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of that Service`
  line `for at least three years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, for the purposes of selecting the Chairperson and other members`
  line `of the Board and for preparing a panel of persons to be considered for appointment as the Technical`
  line `Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas) of the Appellate Tribunal, constitute a Search Committee`
  line `consisting of--`
  line
  line `(i) Member, Planning Commission in charge of the energy sector-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(ii) Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas-Member;`
  line
  line `(iii) Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Finance, Department of Economic AffairsMember;`
  line
  line `(iv) Secretary to the Government of India in charge of Commerce, Ministry of Commerce and`
  line `Industry-Member; and`
  line
  line `(v) Secretary to the Government of India, Department of Legal Affairs, Ministry of Law and`
  line Justice-Member.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10995)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office, conditions of service, etc., of Chairperson and other members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10995&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before`
  line `appointing any person as the Chairperson or other member, the Central Government shall satisfy itself`
  line `that such person does not have any financial or other interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his`
  line `functions as Chairperson or such other member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and other members shall hold office for a term of five years from the date on`
  line `which they enter upon their offices or until they attain the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson and other members shall not be eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, appointment of a member as Chairperson shall not be`
  line `deemed to be re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(3) A person in the service of the Central Government, a State Government or an undertaking,`
  line `corporation or company owned or controlled by the Central Government or a State Government or from`
  line `any other non-Governmental or corporate body shall resign or retire from such service before joining as`
  line `the Chairperson or other member, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson and the other members shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson or any other member shall be varied to his disadvantage after appointment.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson or other member may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the`
  line `Central Government and on such resignation being accepted, the Chairperson or such other member shall`
  line `be deemed to have vacated his office.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson or any other member, upon ceasing to hold office as such, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be ineligible for further employment under the Central Government or any State Government;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) not accept any commercial employment for a period of two years from the date he ceases to`
  line `hold such office.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, "commercial employment" means employment in`
  line `any capacity under, or agency of, a person engaged in trading, commercial, industrial or financial`
  line `business in any field and includes also a director of a company or partner of a firm or setting up practice`
  line `either independently or as partner of a firm or as an advisor or a consultant.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10996)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10996&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall have the powers of general superintendence and`
  line `directions in the conduct of the affairs of the Board and shall, in addition to presiding over the meetings of`
  line `the Board, exercise and discharge such other powers and functions of the Board, as may be assigned to`
  line `him by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10997)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal of Chairperson or any other member from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10997&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may`
  line `remove from office the Chairperson or any other member, who--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged as insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Chairperson or other member shall be removed from office under clause (d) or`
  line `clause (e) unless the Central Government, after holding an inquiry by any person appointed or authority`
  line `constituted for the purpose and in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed in this behalf, is`
  line `satisfied that such person ought on such ground or grounds to be removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10998)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Meetings of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10998&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places, and shall observe`
  line `such procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at such`
  line `meetings) as may be provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or, if he is unable to attend a meeting of the Board, the senior-most member`
  line `present, reckoned from the date of appointment to the Board, shall preside at the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of common date of appointment of members, the member senior in age shall be`
  line `considered as senior to the other members.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `the members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson or in his`
  line `absence, the person presiding shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) All orders and decisions of the Board shall be authenticated by the Secretary or any other officer`
  line `of the Board duly authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10999)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=10999&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Board`
  line `shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (11000)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers and other employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11000&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in consultation`
  line `with the Board, appoint a Secretary to exercise and perform such powers and duties, under the control of the Chairperson as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation shall be necessary for appointment of the first Secretary of the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, with the approval of the Central Government, determine the number, nature and`
  line `categories of other officers and employees required to assist the Board in the efficient discharge of its`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Secretary, the other officers and employees of the Board shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may appoint consultants required to assist in the discharge of its functions on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (11001)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11001&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall--`
  line
  line `(a) protect the interest of consumers by fostering fair trade and competition amongst the entities;`
  line
  line `(b) register entities to--`
  line
  line `(i) market notified petroleum and petroleum products and, subject to the contractual`
  line `obligations of the Central Government, natural gas;`
  line
  line `(ii) establish and operate liquefied natural gas terminals;`
  line
  line `(iii) establish storage facilities for petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas exceeding`
  line `such capacity as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) authorise entities to--`
  line
  line `(i) lay, build, operate or expand a common carrier or contract carrier;`
  line
  line `(ii) lay, build, operate or expand city or local natural gas distribution network;`
  line
  line `(d) declare pipelines as common carrier or contract carrier;`
  line
  line `(e) regulate, by regulations,--`
  line
  line `(i) access to common carrier or contract carrier so as to ensure fair trade and competition`
  line `amongst entities and for that purpose specify pipeline access code;`
  line
  line `(ii) transportation rates for common carrier or contract carrier;`
  line
  line `(iii) access to city or local natural gas distribution network so as to ensure fair trade and`
  line `competition amongst entities as per pipeline access code;`
  line
  line `(f) in respect of notified petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas--`
  line
  line `(i) ensure adequate availability;`
  line
  line `(ii) ensure display of information about the maximum retail prices fixed by the entity for`
  line `consumers at retail outlets;`
  line
  line `(iii) monitor prices and take corrective measures to prevent restrictive trade practice by the`
  line entities;
  line
  line `(iv) secure equitable distribution for petroleum and petroleum products;`
  line
  line `(v) provide, by regulations, and enforce, retail service obligations for retail outlets and`
  line `marketing service obligations for entities;`
  line
  line `(vi) monitor transportation rates and take corrective action to prevent restrictive trade practice`
  line `by the entities;`
  line
  line `(g) levy fees and other charges as determined by regulations;`
  line
  line `(h) maintain a data bank of information on activities relating to petroleum, petroleum products`
  line `and natural gas;`
  line
  line `(i) lay down, by regulations, the technical standards and specifications including safety standards`
  line `in activities relating to petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas, including the construction and`
  line `operation of pipeline and infrastructure projects related to downstream petroleum and natural gas`
  line sector;
  line
  line `(j) perform such other functions as may be entrusted to it by the Central Government to carry out`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (11002)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Powers regarding complaints and resolution of disputes by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11002&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall`
  line `have jurisdiction to--`
  line
  line `(a) adjudicate upon and decide any dispute or matter arising amongst entities or between an entity`
  line `and any other person on issues relating to refining, processing, storage, transportation, distribution,`
  line `marketing and sale of petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas according to the provisions of`
  line `Chapter V, unless the parties have agreed for arbitration;`
  line
  line `(b) receive any complaint from any person and conduct any inquiry and investigation connected`
  line `with the activities relating to petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas on contravention of--`
  line
  line `(i) retail service obligations;`
  line
  line `(ii) marketing service obligations;`
  line
  line `(iii) display of retail price at retail outlets;`
  line
  line `(iv) terms and conditions subject to which a pipeline has been declared as common carrier or`
  line `contract carrier or access for other entities was allowed to a city or local natural gas distribution`
  line `network, or authorisation has been granted to an entity for laying, building, expanding or`
  line `operating a pipeline as common carrier or contract carrier or authorisation has been granted to an`
  line `entity for laying, building, expanding or operating a city or local natural gas distribution network;`
  line
  line `(v) any other provision of this Act or the rules or the regulations or orders made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) While deciding a complaint under sub-section (1), the Board may pass such orders and issue such`
  line `directions as it deems fit or refer the matter for investigation according to the provisions of Chapter V.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (11003)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Procedure of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11003&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall have, for the purposes of discharging its`
  line `functions under this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of`
  line `1872), requisitioning any public record or document or a copy of such record or document, from any`
  line `office and production of such documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) dismissing an application for default or deciding it, ex parte;`
  line
  line `(f) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it, ex`
  line parte;
  line
  line `(g) granting interim relief;`
  line
  line `(h) reviewing its decision; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding before the Board shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860) and the Board shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter`
  line `XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and subject to other provisions of`
  line `this Act and of any rules made thereunder, shall have powers to regulate its own procedure including the`
  line `places at which it shall conduct its business.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (11004)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Register.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11004&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, a register to be called the Petroleum and Natural Gas`
  line `Register shall be kept at the head office of the Board containing such details of entities--`
  line
  line `(a) registered for--`
  line
  line `(i) marketing notified petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas, or`
  line
  line `(ii) establishing and operating liquefied natural gas terminals, or`
  line
  line `(iii) establishing storage facilities for petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas exceeding`
  line `such capacity as may be specified by regulations, or`
  line
  line `(b) authorised for--`
  line
  line `(i) laying, building, operating or expanding a common carrier, or`
  line
  line `(ii) laying, building, operating or expanding a city or local natural gas distribution network, as`
  line `may be provided by the Board by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of any entry in the register purporting to be maintained by the Board and certified as such`
  line `by an officer authorised by the Board, shall be admitted in evidence in all courts and in all proceedings`
  line `without further proof or production of the original.`
  line
  line `(3) The register shall be open to public inspection at the head office of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person may, on application to the Board, and on payment of such fee as may be determined`
  line `by the Board, by regulations, obtain a certified copy of any entry in the register.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (11005)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Registration of entities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11005&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every entity desirous of--`
  line
  line `(a) marketing any notified petroleum or petroleum products or natural gas; or`
  line
  line `(b) establishing or operating a liquefied natural gas terminal; or`
  line
  line `(c) establishing storage facilities for petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas exceeding such`
  line `capacity as may be specified by regulations,`
  line
  line `and fulfilling the eligibility conditions as may be prescribed shall make an application to the Board for its`
  line `registration under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no registration under this Act shall be required for any entity carrying on any activity`
  line `referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) immediately before the appointed day but shall inform`
  line `the Board about such activity within six months from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and in such`
  line `manner and shall be accompanied by such fee as may be determined by the Board by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may, after making such enquiry and subject to such terms and conditions as it may`
  line `specify, grant a certificate of registration to the entity allowing to commence and carry on the activity`
  line `referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c), as the case may be, of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may, by order, suspend or cancel a certificate of registration granted under sub-section`
  line `(3) in such manner as may be determined by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this sub-section shall be made unless the entity concerned has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (11006)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Authorisation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11006&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No entity shall--`
  line
  line `(a) lay, build, operate or expand any pipeline as a common carrier or contract carrier,`
  line
  line `(b) lay, build, operate or expand any city or local natural gas distribution network, without`
  line `obtaining authorisation under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an entity,--`
  line
  line `(i) laying, building, operating or expanding any pipeline as common carrier or contract carrier; or`
  line
  line `(ii) laying, building, operating or expanding any city or local natural gas distribution network,`
  line
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall be deemed to have such authorisation subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, but any change in the purpose or usage shall require separate authorisation`
  line `granted by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (11007)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Application for authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11007&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) An entity which is laying, building, operating or expanding,`
  line `or which proposes to lay, build, operate or expand, a pipeline as a common carrier or contract carrier shall`
  line `apply in writing to the Board for obtaining an authorisation under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an entity laying, building, operating or expanding any pipeline as common carrier or`
  line `contract carrier authorised by the Central Government at any time before the appointed day shall furnish`
  line `the particulars of such activities to the Board within six months from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) An entity which is laying, building, operating or expanding, or which proposes to lay, build,`
  line `operate or expand, a city or local natural gas distribution network shall apply in writing for obtaining an`
  line `authorisation under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an entity laying, building, operating or expanding any city or local natural gas`
  line `distribution network authorised by the Central Government at any time before the appointed day shall`
  line `furnish the particulars of such activities to the Board within six months from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be made in such form and in such`
  line `manner and shall be accompanied with such fee as the Board may, by regulations, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Act and consistent with the norms and policy guidelines laid`
  line `down by the Central Government, the Board may either reject or accept an application made to it, subject`
  line `to such amendments or conditions, if any, as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of refusal or conditional acceptance of an application, the Board shall record in`
  line `writing the grounds for such rejection or conditional acceptance, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (11008)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Publicity of applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11008&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `When an application for registration for marketing notified`
  line `petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas, or for establishing and operating a liquefied natural gas`
  line `terminal, or for establishing storage facilities for petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas exceeding`
  line `such capacity as may be specified by regulations, is accepted whether absolutely or subject to conditions`
  line `or limitations, the Board shall, as soon as may be, cause such acceptance to be known to the public in`
  line `such form and manner as may be provided by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (11009)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Grant of authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11009&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) When, either on the basis of an application for authorisation for`
  line `laying, building, operating or expanding a common carrier or contract carrier or for laying, building,`
  line `operating or expanding a city or local natural gas distribution network is received or on suo motu basis,`
  line `the Board forms an opinion that it is necessary or expedient to lay, build, operate or expand a common`
  line `carrier or contract carrier between two specified points, or to lay, build, operate or expand a city or local`
  line `natural gas distribution network in a specified geographic area, the Board may give wide publicity of its`
  line `intention to do so and may invite applications from interested parties to lay, build, operate or expand such`
  line `pipelines or city or local natural gas distribution network.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may select an entity in an objective and transparent manner as specified by regulations`
  line `for such activities.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (11010)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Declaring, laying, building, etc., of common carrier or contract carrier and city or local natural gas distribution network.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11010&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Board is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient, to`
  line `declare an existing pipeline for transportation of petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas or an`
  line `existing city or local natural gas distribution network, as a common carrier or contract carrier or to`
  line `regulate or allow access to such pipeline or network, it may give wide publicity of its intention to do so`
  line `and invite objections and suggestions within a specified time from all persons and entities likely to be`
  line `affected by such decision.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Board shall provide the entity owning, the pipeline or`
  line `network an opportunity of being heard and fix the terms and conditions subject to which the pipeline or`
  line `network may be declared as a common carrier or contract carrier and pass such orders as it deems fit`
  line `having regard to the public interest, competitive transportation rates and right of first use.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may, after following the procedure as specified by regulations under section 19 and`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2), by notification,--`
  line
  line `(a) declare a pipeline or city or local natural gas distribution network as a common carrier or`
  line `contract carrier; or`
  line
  line `(b) authorise an entity to lay, build, operate or expand a pipeline as a common carrier or contract`
  line `carrier; or`
  line
  line `(c) allow access to common carrier or contract carrier or city or local natural gas distribution`
  line `network; or`
  line
  line `(d) authorise an entity to lay, build, operate or expand a city or local natural gas distribution`
  line network.
  line
  line `(4) The Board may decide on the period of exclusivity to lay, build, operate or expand a city or local`
  line `natural gas distribution network for such number of years as it may by order, determine in accordance`
  line `with the principles laid down by the regulations made by it, in a transparent manner while fully protecting`
  line `the consumer interests.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, the Board shall be guided by the objectives of promoting`
  line `competition among entities, avoiding infructuous investment, maintaining or increasing supplies or for`
  line `securing equitable distribution or ensuring adequate availability of petroleum, petroleum products and`
  line `natural gas throughout the country and follow such principles as the Board may, by regulations, determine`
  line `in carrying out its functions under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (11011)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Right of first use, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11011&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The entity laying, building, operating or expanding a pipeline for`
  line `transportation of petroleum and petroleum products or laying, building, operating or expanding a city or`
  line `local natural gas distribution network shall have right of first use for its own requirement and the`
  line `remaining capacity shall be used amongst entities as the Board may, after issuing a declaration under`
  line `section 20, determine having regard to the needs of fair competition in marketing and availability of`
  line `petroleum and petroleum products throughout the country:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of an entity engaged in both marketing of natural gas and laying, building,`
  line `operating or expanding a pipeline for transportation of natural gas on common carrier or contract carrier`
  line `basis, the Board shall require such entities to comply with the affiliate code of conduct as may be`
  line `specified by regulations and may require such entity to separate the activities of marketing of natural gas`
  line `and the transportation including ownership of the pipeline within such period as may be allowed by the`
  line `Board and only within the said period, such entity shall have right of first use.`
  line
  line `(2) An entity other than an entity authorised to operate shall pay transportation rate for use of`
  line `common carrier or contract carrier to the entity operating it as an authorised entity.`
  line
  line `(3) An entity authorised to lay, build, operate or expand a pipeline as common carrier or contract`
  line `carrier or to lay, build, operate or expand a city or local natural gas distribution network shall be entitled`
  line `to institute proceedings before the Board to prevent, or to recover damages for, the infringement of any`
  line `right relating to authorisation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "infringement of any right" means doing of any`
  line `act by any person which interferes with common carrier or contract carrier or causes prejudice to the`
  line `authorised entity.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (11012)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Transportation tariff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11012&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board shall lay down, by`
  line `regulations, the transportation tariffs for common carriers or contract carriers or city or local natural gas`
  line `distribution network and the manner of determining such tariffs.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Board shall be guided by the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the factors which may encourage competition, efficiency, economic use of the resources,`
  line `good performance and optimum investments;`
  line
  line `(b) safeguard the consumer interest and at the same time recovery of cost of transportation in a`
  line `reasonable manner;`
  line
  line `(c) the principles rewarding efficiency in performance;`
  line
  line `(d) the connected infrastructure such as compressors, pumps, metering units, storage and the like`
  line `connected to the common carriers or contract carriers;`
  line
  line `(e) benchmarking against a reference tariff calculated based on cost of service, internal rate of`
  line `return, net present value or alternate mode of transport;`
  line
  line `(f) policy of the Central Government applicable to common carrier, contract carrier and city or`
  line `local distribution natural gas network.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (11013)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Suspension or cancellation of authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11013&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If the Board, on an application of an affected`
  line `party or on its own motion, is satisfied that the entity in favour of which authorisation has been granted`
  line `under section 19 has failed to comply with any conditions of authorisation, it may, after giving an`
  line `opportunity to such entity of being heard, either suspend the authorisation for such period as the Board`
  line `may think fit or cancel the authorisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Board is of the opinion that an authorised entity persistently acts in a manner`
  line `prejudicial to the interests of consumers, it may take action for the suspension of the authorisation`
  line `immediately subject to the opportunity of hearing being given subsequently, after which action so taken`
  line `may be confirmed or revoked.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (11014)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Board to settle disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11014&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided for arbitration in the relevant`
  line `agreements between entities or between an entity or any other person, as the case may be, if any dispute`
  line `arises, in respect of matters referred to in sub-section (2) among entities or between an entity and any`
  line `other person, such dispute shall be decided by a Bench consisting of the Member (Legal) and one or more`
  line `members nominated by the Chairperson:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the members of the Bench differ on any point or points, they shall state the point or`
  line `points on which they differ and refer the same to a member other than a member of the Bench for hearing`
  line `on such point or points and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of that member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bench constituted under sub-section (1) shall exercise, on and from the appointed day, all`
  line `such jurisdiction, powers and authority as were exercisable by a civil court on any matter relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) refining, processing, storage, transportation and distribution of petroleum, petroleum products`
  line `and natural gas by the entities;`
  line
  line `(b) marketing and sale of petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas including the quality of`
  line `service and security of supply to the consumers by the entities; and`
  line
  line `(c) registration or authorisation issued by the Board under section 15 or section 19.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), the Board`
  line `shall have the power to decide matters referred to in sub-section (2) on or after the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (11015)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Filing of complaints.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11015&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) A complaint may be filed before the Board by any person in respect`
  line `of matters relating to entities or between entities on any matter arising out of the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the complaints of individual consumers maintainable before a consumer disputes`
  line `redressal forum under the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) shall not be taken up by the Board`
  line `but shall be heard and disposed of by such forum.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "consumer disputes redressal`
  line `forum" shall mean the district forum, State Commission or, the National Commission, as the case may be,`
  line `constituted under the provisions of the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986).`
  line
  line `(2) Every complaint made under sub-section (1) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on`
  line `which any act or conduct constituting a contravention took place and shall be in such form and shall be`
  line `accompanied by such fee as may be provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may entertain a complaint after the expiry of the said period if it is satisfied`
  line `that there was sufficient cause for not filing the complaint within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of a complaint under sub-section (1), the Board shall decide within thirty days whether`
  line `there is a prima facie case against the entity or entities concerned and may either conduct enquiry on its`
  line `own or refer the matter for investigation under this Chapter, to an Investigating Officer having`
  line `jurisdiction; and, where the matter is referred to such Investigating Officer, on receipt of a report from`
  line `such Investigating Officer, the Board may, hear and dispose of the complaint as a dispute if it falls under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 27 and in any other case, it may pass such orders and issue such directions as it`
  line `deems fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Central Government considers that a matter arising out of the provisions of this Act is`
  line `required to be investigated, it shall make a reference to the Board and the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `apply as if such reference were a complaint made to the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (11016)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to investigate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11016&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of provisions of section 25, the Board shall, subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (3), appoint by general or special order, an officer of the Board as an`
  line `Investigating Officer for holding an investigation in the manner provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Board considers it necessary that the matter should be investigated by any`
  line `investigating agency of the State or Central Government including the special police force constituted`
  line `under section 2 of the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946), the Board may request`
  line `the concerned Government for directing or authorising such agency to investigate and the agency so`
  line `directed or authorised shall, then, be competent to exercise the powers and to discharge the duties of an`
  line `Investigating Officer under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be appointed as an Investigating Officer unless he possesses such qualifications`
  line `and experience as may be determined by the Board by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Where more than one Investigating Officer is appointed, the Board shall specify, by order, the`
  line `matters and the local limits of jurisdiction with respect to which each such officer shall exercise his`
  line jurisdiction.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (11017)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Factors to be taken into account by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11017&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall, while deciding a dispute`
  line `under this Chapter, have due regard to the provisions of this Act and to the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of disproportionate gain made or unfair advantage derived, wherever quantifiable,`
  line `as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of loss caused to an entity as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(c) the repetitive nature of the default.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (11018)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Civil penalty for contravention of directions given by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11018&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `In case any complaint is`
  line `filed before the Board by any person or if the Board is satisfied that any person has contravened a`
  line `direction issued by the Board under this Act to provide access to, or to adhere to the transportation rate in`
  line `respect of a common carrier, or to display maximum retail price at retail outlets, or violates the terms and conditions subject to which registration or authorisation has been granted under section 15 or section 19`
  line `or the retail service obligations or marketing service obligations, or does not furnish information,`
  line `document, return of report required by the Board, it may, after giving such person an opportunity of being`
  line `heard in the matter, by order in writing, direct that, without prejudice to any other penalty to which he`
  line `may be liable under this Act, such person shall pay, by way of civil penalty an amount which shall not`
  line `exceed one crore rupees for each contravention and in case of a continuing failure with additional penalty`
  line `which may extend to ten lakh rupees for every day during which the failure continues after contravention`
  line `of the first such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a complaint on restrictive trade practice, the amount of civil penalty may`
  line `extend to five times the unfair gains made by the entity or ten crore rupees, whichever is higher.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (11019)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Orders passed by Board deemed to be decrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11019&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every order made by the Board under this`
  line `Act shall, on a certificate issued by an officer of the Board, shall be executable in the same manner as if it`
  line `were a decree of a civil court:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an appeal lies against an order of the Board and no appeal is preferred then the`
  line `order of the Board shall be deemed to be a final decree under this section on the expiry of the period`
  line `allowed for preferring an appeal against such order before the Appellate Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (11020)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11020&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `established under section 110 of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003) shall be the Appellate Tribunal for`
  line `the purposes of this Act and the said Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the jurisdiction, powers and`
  line `authority conferred on it by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Technical Member of the Appellate Tribunal for the purposes of this Act shall be`
  line `called the Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas) and shall have the qualifications specified in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 31.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003), the Central`
  line `Government may, for the purposes of this Act, appoint one or more Technical Members (Petroleum and`
  line `Natural Gas) on the Appellate Tribunal for Electricity or designate a Technical Member of the said`
  line `Tribunal having the qualifications specified in sub-section (2) of section 31 and when a Technical`
  line `Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas) is appointed, he shall be in addition to the three other members`
  line `appointed under the said Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (11021)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11021&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Technical Member (Petroleum and`
  line `Natural Gas) shall be appointed from the panel prepared by the Search Committee constituted under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural`
  line `Gas) of the Appellate Tribunal unless he--`
  line
  line `(i) is, or has been, a Secretary for at least one year in the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government having adequate experience in energy sector, especially in matters relating to Petroleum`
  line `and Natural Gas sector; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is, or has been, a person of ability and standing, having adequate knowledge or experience in`
  line `dealing with matters relating to exploration, production, transmission pipelines, marketing or`
  line `regulation of petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas, economics, commerce, law or`
  line management.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (11022)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Terms and conditions of service of Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11022&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line The
  line `term of office, the salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas) shall be the same as applicable to the other members of`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (11023)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11023&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order or decision made by the`
  line `Board under this Act may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person preferring an appeal against an order or decision of the Board levying any`
  line `penalty shall, while filing the appeal, deposit the amount of such penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where in any particular case, the Appellate Tribunal is of the opinion that`
  line `deposit of such penalty would cause undue hardship to such person, it may dispense with such deposit`
  line `subject to such conditions as it may deem fit to impose so as to safeguard the realisation of penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of thirty days from the date on`
  line `which a copy of the direction or order of decision made by the Board is received by the aggrieved person`
  line `and it shall be in such form, verified in such manner and be accompanied by such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal and`
  line `to the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal filed under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by the Appellate Tribunal as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavor shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within ninety`
  line `days from the date of receipt of appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such appeal could not be disposed of within the said period of ninety days,`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the appeal within the said`
  line period.
  line
  line `(6) The Appellate Tribunal may, for the purpose of examining the legality or propriety or correctness`
  line `of any order or decision of the Board referred to in the appeal filed under sub-section (1), either on its`
  line `own motion or otherwise, call for the records relevant to disposing of such appeal and make such orders`
  line `as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (11024)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Procedure and powers of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11024&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 120 to 124`
  line `(both inclusive) of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003) shall mutatis mutandis apply to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal in the discharge of its functions under this Act as they apply to it in the discharge of its functions`
  line `under the Electricity Act, 2003.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (11025)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Appellate Tribunal to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11025&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Appellate Tribunal may, by notification,`
  line `make rules consistent with the provisions of this Act as to the conduct and procedure in respect of all`
  line `proceedings before it under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (11026)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Orders passed by Appellate Tribunal to be executable as a decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11026&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every order made by`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by the Appellate Tribunal as a decree of a civil`
  line `court, and for this purpose, the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if it`
  line `were a decree made by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (11027)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11027&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or in any other law, an appeal shall lie against any order, not being an`
  line `interlocutory order, of the Appellate Tribunal to the Supreme Court on one or more of the grounds`
  line `specified in section 100 of that Code.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie against any decision or order made by the Appellate Tribunal with the consent`
  line `of the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of ninety days from the date of`
  line `the decision or order appealed against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of ninety`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in`
  line time.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (11028)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11028&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Board grants of such sums of money as are required to`
  line `pay salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and the other members and the administrative`
  line `expenses including the salaries, allowances and pensions payable to the officers and employees of the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (11029)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Fund.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11029&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the Petroleum and Natural Gas`
  line `Regulatory Board Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(i) all grants, fees, penalties and charges received by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) all sums received by the Board from such other sources as may be approved by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for making payments towards--`
  line
  line `(i) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and other members and the`
  line `administrative expenses including the salaries, allowances and pensions payable to the officers and`
  line `employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expenses incurred or to be incurred in carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall--`
  line
  line `(i) constitute a committee consisting of such persons as it thinks fit to recommend to that`
  line `Government the budgetary requirements of the Board for salaries, allowances and all other expenses;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) fix the budgetary ceiling of the Board on the basis of the recommendations of the committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (11030)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11030&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the decisions of the Board taken`
  line `in the discharge of its functions under this Act, being matters appealable to the Appellate Tribunal, shall`
  line `not be subject to audit under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right`
  line `to demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and`
  line `inspection of offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (11031)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Annual report and its laying before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11031&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall prepare once every year`
  line `in such form and at such time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a summary of its activities`
  line `including information relating to the proceedings and policies during the previous years and such report`
  line `shall also contain statements of annual accounts of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report shall be forwarded to the Central Government and the Central Government`
  line `shall cause such report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (11032)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11032&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time, by writing issue to the Board such directions as it may think necessary in the interest of the`
  line `sovereignty and integrity of India, the security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States or public`
  line order.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the foregoing provision, the Central Government may, if it finds necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do in public interest or for maintaining or increasing supplies of petroleum, petroleum`
  line `products or natural gas or all or any of them or for securing their equitable distribution and ensuring`
  line `adequate availability, issue policy directives to the Board in writing and such policy directives shall be`
  line `binding upon the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such directive shall relate to any day-to-day affairs of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity of expressing its`
  line `views before any directive is issued under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (11033)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Taking over control and management of facilities and business premises of any entity and retail outlets in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11033&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of war or natural calamity or such other similar`
  line `circumstances leading to disruption of supply of petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas, the Central`
  line `Government may, for ensuring the continuous supply of petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas, by`
  line `notification, either take over the control and management of any storage site, facilities and business`
  line `premises of any entity and retail outlets or suspend its operations or entrust, to any agency of the Central`
  line `or State Government for such time and manage it in such manner, as may be specified in that notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the affected entities shall be given an opportunity of being heard before issuing orders`
  line `to take over the control and management of retail outlets and other business premises:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of any urgency or in cases where the circumstances do not permit`
  line `serving of notice for want of sufficient time or otherwise upon the entity against whom the order is`
  line `directed, the opportunity of hearing may be dispensed with in public interest in order to maintain the`
  line `uninterrupted supply of petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas for a specified period.`
  line
  line `(2) The collector of the revenue district in which the property referred to in the notification issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) is situated shall determine the amount of compensation payable for taking over of`
  line `the property.`
  line
  line `(3) The form and manner in which an application for claiming compensation under this section shall`
  line `be made, the procedure for determining the compensation and the time within which such compensation`
  line `shall be payable, shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (11034)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Punishment for contravention of directions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11034&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If a person contravenes the`
  line `directions of the Board, such person shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty-five crore`
  line `rupees and in case of continuing contravention with additional fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees`
  line `for every day during which the contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (11035)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for wilful failure to comply with orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11035&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `willfully fails to comply with the order of the Appellate Tribunal, he shall be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to one crore rupees and in case of a second or subsequent offence with fine which may extend`
  line `to two crore rupees and in the case of continuing contravention with additional fine which may extend to`
  line `twenty lakh rupees for every day during which such default continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (11036)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Punishment for unauthorised activities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11036&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being an entity, markets any notified`
  line `petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas without a valid registration, or authorisation such person`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three years or with fine which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five crore rupees or with both, and in case of continuing contravention with additional fine which`
  line `may extend to ten lakh rupees for every day during which the contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (11037)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Punishment for establishing or operating a liquefied natural gas terminal without registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11037&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `If a person establishes or operates a liquefied natural gas terminal without registration as`
  line `required under section 15, such person shall be liable for punishment with an imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years or penalty of twenty-five crore rupees or with both, and in case of`
  line `continuing contravention with additional fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees for every day during`
  line `which the contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (11038)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Punishment for laying, building, operating or expanding a common carrier or contract carrier without authorisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11038&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `If a person lays, builds, operates or expands a common carrier or`
  line `contract carrier or a city or local natural gas distribution network without obtaining authorisation required`
  line `under section 19, such person shall be liable for punishment with an imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or penalty of twenty-five crore rupees or with both, and in case of continuing`
  line `contravention with additional fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees for every day during which the`
  line `contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (11039)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Punishment for wilful damages to common carrier or contract carrier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11039&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Every person who`
  line `willfully removes, destroys or damages any pipeline or city or local natural gas distribution network or`
  line `other work of the common carrier or contract carrier for supplying petroleum, petroleum products or`
  line `natural gas shall for each such offence be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three years`
  line `or with fine which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees or with both, and, in case of continuing`
  line `contravention with additional fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees for every day during which such`
  line `contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (11040)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11040&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he has exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line 'committed by a company and it is proved `that the offence has been committed with the consent or'
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (11041)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Maintenance of data bank and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11041&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain a data bank and`
  line `information system relating to activities of entities dealing with petroleum, petroleum products and`
  line `natural gas in such form and manner as may be provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall have power to verify the data supplied by the entities and appoint any person or`
  line `persons for the purpose and take such measures as it may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (11042)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Obligations of entities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11042&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every entity shall--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain such documentary records as may be specified by the Board by regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) allow inspection of such facilities and documentary records, as may be specified by the Board,`
  line `by any person authorised by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) commence operation of activities for which authorisation has been granted within such period`
  line `as may be specified by the Board in the document of authorisation;`
  line
  line `(d) register--`
  line
  line `(i) agreements with the Board relating to use of pipelines for supply of petroleum, petroleum`
  line `products and natural gas; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other document which the Board may determine by regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) comply with marketing service obligations and retail service obligations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may call for any information from any entity including information which is`
  line `considered necessary for ensuring transparency or ascertaining true ownership of the entity.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board or any officer authorised by the Board shall have the power to inspect and obtain`
  line `information, wherever necessary, from the entities.`
  line
  line `(4) For the effective enforcement of the terms and conditions of authorisation, the Board or any`
  line `officer authorised by it for that purpose, shall have all the powers of an inspecting officer as provided`
  line `under section 209A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(5) It shall be the duty of every entity to carry out the directions of the Board given under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall maintain confidentiality in respect of any information and record received by it`
  line `from the entities and shall not disclose information contained therein to any person or authority except on`
  line `the grounds of public interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (11043)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Furnishing of returns, etc., to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11043&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall furnish to the Central`
  line `Government at such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central`
  line `Government may direct, such returns and statements and such particulars in regard to any matter in`
  line `connection with proposed or existing activities under this Act, as the Central Government may, from time`
  line `to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (11044)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Chairperson, members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11044&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members, Officers and`
  line `other employees of the Board and Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas) of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (11045)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11045&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, Board, Technical Authority or Appellate Tribunal or any officer of`
  line `the Central Government or any Chairperson, Member, officer or other employee of the Board or`
  line `Technical Member (Petroleum and Natural Gas) of the Appellate Tribunal for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (11046)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Civil courts not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11046&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit`
  line `or proceeding in respect of any matter which the Board or the Appellate Tribunal is empowered by or`
  line `under this Act to determine, and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect`
  line `of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (11047)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Cognizance of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11047&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable`
  line `under Chapter IX save on a complaint made by the Board or by any investigating agency directed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or of a Chief Judicial Magistrate shall`
  line `try any offence punishable under Chapter IX.`
  line
  line `(3) Every offence punishable under sections 44, 45, 46 and 47 shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (11048)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11048&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any member or`
  line `officer of the Board subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers`
  line `and functions under this Act (except the power to settle a dispute under Chapter VI and to make`
  line `regulations under section 61), as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (11049)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11049&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as it may deem necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (11050)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11050&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to and the other conditions of service of the Chairperson`
  line `and the other members under sub-section (4) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for appointment of any person or constitution of any authority and conducting`
  line `inquiry under section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Secretary, officers and other employees of the Board, under sub-section (3) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter in respect of which the Board may exercise the powers of a civil court under`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(e) the eligibility conditions which an entity shall fulfill for registration under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(f) the form of appeal and the manner of verifying such form, and the fee which shall accompany`
  line `such form, under sub-section (2) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the accounts of the Board shall be maintained under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 40;`
  line
  line `(h) the time and manner in which the annual report of the Board shall be prepared under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner in which applications for claiming compensation shall be made, the`
  line `procedure for determining the compensation and the time within which such compensation shall be`
  line `payable, under sub-section (3) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(j) the time and manner in which returns and statements are to be furnished by the Board to the`
  line `Central Government under section 53;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (11051)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power of Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11051&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by notification, make regulations`
  line `consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time and places of meetings of the Board and the procedure (including quorum necessary`
  line `for the transaction of business) to be followed at such meetings under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the Secretary under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of the consultants appointed under sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) the capacity of storage facilities for petroleum, petroleum products or natural gas requiring`
  line `registration under sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating open access to and transportation rate for the common carrier or contract carrier or`
  line `city or local natural gas distribution network and other matters referred to in clause (e) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) marketing service obligations for entities and retail service obligations for retail outlets under`
  line `sub-clause (v) of clause (f) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) levy of fees and other charges under clause (g) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(h) the technical standards and specifications including safety standards in activities relating to`
  line `petroleum, petroleum products and natural gas under clause (i) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure to be followed by the Board including the places at which it shall conduct its`
  line `business under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of maintaining the Petroleum and Natural Gas Register under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and manner of making application for obtaining certified copy of any entry in the`
  line `register and the fee which shall accompany such application, under sub-section (4) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(l) the form and manner in which an application under sub-section (1) of section 15 shall be made`
  line `and the fee which shall accompany such application under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner by which a certificate of registration granted under sub-section (3) of section 15`
  line `may be suspended or cancelled under sub-section (4) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(n) the form and manner in which an application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 17 shall be made and the fee which shall accompany such application under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner in which publicity of acceptance of applications for registration shall be`
  line `made under section 18;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of selection of an entity under sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(q) the principles for determining the number of years for which a city or local natural gas`
  line `distribution network shall be excluded from the purview of a common carrier or contract carrier under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(r) the guiding principles to be followed by the Board and the objectives for declaring, or`
  line `authorising to lay, build, operate or expand a common carrier or contract carrier for declaring, or`
  line `authorising to lay, build, operate or expand a city or local natural gas distribution network, under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(s) the affiliate code of conduct under which the entities are required to comply with under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(t) the transportation tariffs for common carriers or contract carriers or city or local natural gas`
  line `distribution network and the manner of determining such tariffs under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(u) the form in which a complaint may be made and the fee which shall accompany such`
  line `complaint, under sub-section (2) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of holding an investigation by an Investigating Officer under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(w) the qualifications and experience which any person for appointment as an Investigating`
  line `Officer shall possess, under sub-section (2) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(x) the form and manner of maintaining data bank and information system by the Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(y) maintenance of documentary records by an entity, under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 52;`
  line
  line `(z) any other type of documents which are to be registered with the Board under sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(za) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be or may be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (11052)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11052&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government and every regulation made by the Board under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should`
  line `not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (11053)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Transitional arrangements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867&sectionId=11053&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00006_200619_1517807324867
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the commencement of this Act, an agreement`
  line `or agreements have been entered into between one oil company and another for the purpose of sharing of`
  line `petroleum products or sharing of infrastructure facilities among the oil companies and such agreements`
  line `have been approved by the Central Government, the Board may monitor the implementation of such`
  line `agreements for the transition period.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall monitor setting up of dealerships and distributorships of motor spirit, high speed`
  line `diesel, superior kerosene oil, liquefied petroleum gas and CNG stations for natural gas during transition`
  line `period by the entities without encroaching on the retail network of the existing entities.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "transition period" shall mean a`
  line `period of three years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this section, "infrastructure facilities" shall mean facilities at`
  line `ports, refineries, terminals, depots and aviation fuelling stations including hydrant lines and shall include`
  line `loading and unloading facilities.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.--For the purposes of this section "encroaching" includes taking over of retail outlet`
  line `of one entity by another.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
